main event: A person reported seeing multiple star-like objects moving in the sky on various dates in 1967.
interesting points: The witness reported seeing the objects at different times of the night, from 5:15 PM to 11:15 PM, and on different dates from January to July 1967.
The witness believed the objects were satellites, and the Air Force confirmed that the sightings corresponded to the paths of known satellites like Echo I and Echo II.
The Air Force stated that when photographing these satellites, a time exposure would be needed to improve the quality of the pictures, as they would otherwise just appear as point sources of light.
The Air Force did not feel it was necessary to conduct any photo analysis due to the poor quality of the photographs provided.
There were several other UFO reports and letters received, but the Air Force felt it was too late to conduct interviews with the individuals involved.
sighted object: star-like objects moving in the sky
